Workout Wednesday! Part ✌🏼of my continued TRX workouts for you this week. These ones are a bit slower and controlled (which are always much harder for me 😅) Cue my epic fail at the end. That one looked so much easier than it was. Tag a friend and give this one a whirl 🎉 Part 2 is 5 exercises. Try 30-45 seconds each/15 second recovery before moving to the next. Challenge = change 🙌🏼💪🏼
.
1) Alternating back taps (push-up position)
2) Upper row
3) Single leg pistol squat jumps
4) Negative plank drops to plank ups (walk back forward)
5) Pike ups to pike push-up
Most of these are SLOW and controlled core movements so even if you want to do them fast, you'll have to slow down in order to complete. Just a little tip for your first time trying. And I'm sure some of you will BEAST these so disregard 😂💪🏼
.
